parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Failure to Honor Recall for Cam Shaft Position Sensor
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure to honor the recall for the cam shaft position sensor can lead to engine stalling, decreased engine performance, and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: Check engine light remains on
engine stalling
decreased engine performance.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Unavailability of Parts for Cam Shaft Position Sensor Recall
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unavailability of parts for the cam shaft position sensor recall can lead to delayed or incomplete repairs, potentially causing accidents or engine damage.
symptoms: Delayed or incomplete repairs
unavailability of parts.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Engine fire can cause serious damage to the vehicle, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Engine caught on fire
smoke coming out of the vents
flames coming out of the engine.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hoses can cause the brakes to fail, leading to accidents or loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: The brake pedal goes to the floor
the vehicle continues to accelerate despite applying the brakes
the vehicle rolls when applying the brakes
the brakes fail to operate.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The inability to obtain recall repair for the brake hose failure can lead to continued risk of brake failure, accidents, and loss of control of the vehicle.
symptoms: Difficulty finding a dealership to honor the recall
lack of parts for the recall repair
dealership refusal to perform recall repair due to vehicle not being purchased from their dealership.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Lack of Power and Acceleration Issues
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The lack of power and acceleration issues can cause the vehicle to struggle to reach normal speeds, making it difficult to merge onto highways, climb hills, or maintain speed on inclines, which can increase the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle has no power
the accelerator pedal must be pushed to the floor to reach moderate speeds (e.g.
45 mph)
the vehicle struggles to accelerate
the vehicle has difficulty maintaining speed on inclines.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The improper tire spin and alignment can cause uneven tire wear, reduced traction, and loss of control, which can increase the risk of accidents, especially on wet or slippery roads.
symptoms: The tires spin improperly
the vehicle pulls to one side
the tires wear unevenly
the vehicle vibrates or shakes while driving.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Using the incorrect fuel type can cause engine damage, reduce fuel efficiency, and affect vehicle performance, which can lead to costly repairs and potentially cause accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle has reduced power or performance
the engine misfires or stalls
the vehicle's fuel efficiency is lower than expected.
